but take my word for it.

942
00:59:08,210 --> 00:59:10,690
Matt Drayton really stands
for something in this town.

943
00:59:10,770 --> 00:59:13,490
Yes. I know the Guardian's
always been a very good paper.

944
00:59:13,570 --> 00:59:16,010
It's a great paper,
and he made it what it is.

945
00:59:16,050 --> 00:59:20,210
There's never been a public issue on
which Matt Drayton didn't take a stand.

946
00:59:20,250 --> 00:59:23,090
When exactly are you flying over?
Sometime next week?

947
00:59:23,170 --> 00:59:24,970
Just as soon
as I can arrange everything.

948
00:59:25,050 --> 00:59:27,850
Why next week? Why aren't you
flying over with John?

949
00:59:28,690 --> 00:59:30,690
Why am I not flying over with you?

950
00:59:33,610 --> 00:59:35,490
- Is your passport in order?
- Yes.

951
00:59:35,530 --> 00:59:38,090
- Do you need clothes or anything?
- Nothing I couldn't get over there.

952
00:59:38,170 --> 00:59:42,810
Then it seems crazy for you to be
going alone when you could go together.

953
00:59:42,890 --> 00:59:46,450
- Why don't you both leave tonight?
- Why not?

954
01:00:00,610 --> 01:00:03,370
It's 6:00. In an hour
they'll all be here for dinner.

955
01:00:03,450 --> 01:00:05,530
The doctor's plane leaves
at 10:45.

956
01:00:05,610 --> 01:00:10,330
No matter what it is, you're going
to have to tell them how you feel.

957
01:00:11,210 --> 01:00:14,090
I need more than one day
to make a decision like that.

958
01:00:14,170 --> 01:00:16,250
It's the silliest thing
I ever heard of.

959
01:00:16,290 --> 01:00:17,770
But I'll tell you this.

960
01:00:17,850 --> 01:00:20,890
I am not going to try to pretend
that I'm happy about the whole thing...

961
01:00:20,970 --> 01:00:22,370
because I'm not.

962
01:00:22,450 --> 01:00:25,770
And if the doctor's decision
depends upon that, then too bad.

963
01:00:26,690 --> 01:00:29,050
And I'm thinking only
of Joey's welfare.

964
01:00:29,130 --> 01:00:32,450
I have nothing against him personally,
but he's a grown man.

965
01:00:32,530 --> 01:00:36,490
He behaved irresponsibly in the first
place by letting this thing happen.

966
01:00:36,530 --> 01:00:39,250
Now he wants me to be happy
about a situation...

967
01:00:39,330 --> 01:00:42,850
when I happen to know that they'll both
get their brains knocked out.

968
01:00:42,930 --> 01:00:44,890
I'm sorry,
but that's the way I feel.

969
01:00:45,930 --> 01:00:47,690
And I know how you're reacting.

970
01:00:47,730 --> 01:00:51,050
You're so wrapped up in Joey's
excitement over the whole thing...

971
01:00:51,130 --> 01:00:53,690
that you are not behaving
in her best interest!

972
01:02:22,090 --> 01:02:23,450
Yes, Mom.

973
01:02:23,530 --> 01:02:25,650
But there wasn't any reason
not to go tonight.

974
01:02:25,730 --> 01:02:27,610
You can understand,
can't you, Mom?

975
01:02:27,690 --> 01:02:30,970
My passport's in order. There's
nothing at all that I really need.

976
01:02:31,050 --> 01:02:33,050
And it won't
take me an hour to pack.

977
01:02:33,130 --> 01:02:37,330
I'll be able to be with him.
We'll be together the whole time.

978
01:02:37,370 --> 01:02:39,370
Mom, they're here.

979
01:02:39,450 --> 01:02:41,050
I can see them.

980
01:02:41,130 --> 01:02:43,170
They look like awfully nice people.

981
01:02:43,250 --> 01:02:45,170
His mother looks lovely.

982
01:02:45,250 --> 01:02:47,370
You break it to Dad for me,
will you?

983
01:02:48,370 --> 01:02:50,450
Well...

984
01:02:50,530 --> 01:02:53,970
I guess I should have called you back
because there is this one thing...

985
01:02:54,050 --> 01:02:56,490
I should have...

986
01:02:56,530 --> 01:02:59,290
I've been meaning
to write to you about it.

987
01:02:59,330 --> 01:03:02,130
There was one thing
I didn't explain, Dad.

988
01:03:02,170 --> 01:03:04,170
And...

989
01:03:04,250 --> 01:03:06,210
I'm afraid it's gonna be
kind of a shock.

990
01:03:13,810 --> 01:03:16,130
You see what I mean?

991
01:03:16,170 --> 01:03:19,890
Mom, Dad,
this is Joanna Drayton.

992
01:03:19,970 --> 01:03:21,690
Joanna, my mom and dad.

993
01:03:21,730 --> 01:03:24,650
Mrs. Prentice, I'm so happy.

994
01:03:24,690 --> 01:03:27,530
- Miss Drayton?
- Yes.

995
01:03:27,610 --> 01:03:30,690
Mr. Prentice,
I'm very pleased to meet you.

996
01:03:35,410 --> 01:03:37,330
I can explain.

997
01:03:37,410 --> 01:03:41,730
I can imagine what's going on
in your mind...

998
01:03:41,810 --> 01:03:45,010
but we can explain.

999
01:03:46,170 --> 01:03:47,490
You can?

1000
01:03:47,570 --> 01:03:49,730
Of course we can.

1001
01:03:49,810 --> 01:03:52,170
You have bags?

1002
01:03:52,210 --> 01:03:55,930
Of course you have bags.
Let's go get your bags.

1003
01:03:56,010 --> 01:03:57,850
Mama?

1004
01:04:01,770 --> 01:04:03,930
- What did your folks say?
- All's well.

1005
01:04:03,970 --> 01:04:06,290
- Did you talk to your father?
- To Mom. But she'll tell him.

1006
01:04:08,650 --> 01:04:10,530
Tonight?

1007
01:04:10,530 --> 01:04:12,810
- I thought I ought to tell you.
- That's out of the question.

1008
01:04:12,890 --> 01:04:15,290
This whole damn thing is...
No, that's out of the question.

1009
01:04:15,370 --> 01:04:17,410
I'll tell you something else.
I couldn't do what you're about to do...

1010
01:04:17,490 --> 01:04:20,650
so I don't begin to understand
how you propose to go about it.

1011
01:04:20,730 --> 01:04:23,050
But you can't break their hearts
over a drink...

1012
01:04:23,130 --> 01:04:25,010
and expect them
to sit down to dinner.

1013
01:04:25,050 --> 01:04:27,770
Don't you think I know that?

1014
01:04:27,850 --> 01:04:30,690
I have to talk to the doctor...
I'll talk to him after dinner.

1015
01:04:30,770 --> 01:04:32,610
Tell him exactly how I feel.

1016
01:04:34,810 --> 01:04:36,730
I'm not trying
to give you an argument.

1017
01:04:36,770 --> 01:04:39,050
There's nothing I can say
that you don't know.

1018
01:04:39,090 --> 01:04:42,410
It's important that you understand
just how wrong I think you...

1019
01:04:42,490 --> 01:04:44,890
I believe you're making the worst
mistake you've ever made in your...

1020
01:04:44,930 --> 01:04:47,610
You're gonna regret it with more
bitterness that you've ever known...

1021
01:04:47,690 --> 01:04:49,250
for as long as you live.

1022
01:04:49,330 --> 01:04:52,170
You're wrong.
You're as wrong as you can be.

1023
01:04:52,210 --> 01:04:54,530
Because I'm thinking of her
and even the doctor is going to know...

1024
01:04:54,530 --> 01:04:56,450
I'm thinking of her.

1025
01:04:56,530 --> 01:04:58,370
There's something else.

1026
01:04:59,450 --> 01:05:01,490
I'm surprised
it hasn't occurred to you.

1027
01:05:01,570 --> 01:05:03,530
The doctor will accept
whatever you say to him...

1028
01:05:03,610 --> 01:05:07,690
because he's a terribly sensitive man
and because he said he would.

1029
01:05:07,770 --> 01:05:10,490
But Joey won't. The most obvious
mistake you're making...

1030
01:05:10,530 --> 01:05:13,010
is in underestimating
your own daughter.

1031
01:05:13,050 --> 01:05:15,410
She'll fight you and
your whole attitude...

1032
01:05:15,490 --> 01:05:18,250
and everything you do and every
argument you ever try to give her.

1033
01:05:18,970 --> 01:05:20,890
And one thing more.

1034
01:05:20,970 --> 01:05:25,450
Until today, I would never have believed
that I could say such a thing...

1035
01:05:25,530 --> 01:05:27,570
but when she fights you...

1036
01:05:27,650 --> 01:05:29,490
and for what it may be worth...

1037
01:05:29,570 --> 01:05:31,410
I'm going to be on her side.

1038
01:05:36,210 --> 01:05:39,370
I never believed I'd hear you
say a thing like that.

1039
01:05:43,650 --> 01:05:46,970
- Can I get you another drink?
- No, thanks. I'll get it myself.

1040
01:05:53,210 --> 01:05:55,650
I wish we had more time.

1041
01:05:56,930 --> 01:05:58,050
What, Mom?

1042
01:05:58,130 --> 01:06:02,330
I was going to ask Miss Drayton
how her father and mother reacted to...

1043
01:06:02,410 --> 01:06:04,450
Yeah. I wanted to ask that too.

1044
01:06:04,530 --> 01:06:07,650
Please call me Joanna.
They were shaken, all right.

1045
01:06:07,730 --> 01:06:09,850
I don't think
I've ever seen them so surprised.

1046
01:06:09,930 --> 01:06:11,770
The thing that really shook them...

1047
01:06:11,850 --> 01:06:14,690
was that I wanted to marry anybody
they hadn't even heard about.

1048
01:06:14,770 --> 01:06:17,610
I can't blame them
for being sort of stunned by it all.

1049
01:06:17,690 --> 01:06:22,370
Well. Then you couldn't blame us if we
were a little stunned, too, could you?

1050
01:06:22,450 --> 01:06:25,090
I mean, I wouldn't appear unreasonable
if I suggested...

1051
01:06:25,170 --> 01:06:29,130
that the two of you were behaving like
a couple of escaped lunatics, would I?

1052
01:06:31,410 --> 01:06:33,330
This whole thing...

1053
01:06:33,370 --> 01:06:35,290
happened so quickly...

1054
01:06:35,370 --> 01:06:37,210
it's like trying to ride a rocket.

1055
01:06:37,290 --> 01:06:40,210
We didn't plan it that way.
It just happened that way.

1056
01:06:40,290 --> 01:06:44,090
It's a little hard on Joanna's folks and
I'm sure it's gonna be hard on you.

1057
01:06:45,530 --> 01:06:47,210
We've got one evening
to discuss it...

1058
01:06:47,290 --> 01:06:50,210
and if you have any objections,
you'd better raise them in a hurry...

1059
01:06:50,290 --> 01:06:53,490
because in exactly four hours
we're gonna be on that plane and gone.

1060
01:06:53,530 --> 01:06:56,930
I don't think I could list
all my objections in four hours.

1061
01:06:57,010 --> 01:06:59,170
I think I'd need
more like eight hours.

1062
01:06:59,250 --> 01:07:02,530
Well, you've only got four hours.

1063
01:07:02,610 --> 01:07:04,810
So you'll just have to talk
twice as fast.

1064
01:07:20,730 --> 01:07:22,650
Hello, darling.
How are you?

1065
01:07:22,730 --> 01:07:24,930
Forgive me.
I am a little bit early.

1066
01:07:25,010 --> 01:07:27,770
Ego absolvo te.
Come in.

1067
01:07:27,850 --> 01:07:31,330
I don't like to be
always repeating myself...

1068
01:07:31,410 --> 01:07:33,730
but how long is it since
that I remarked that I thought...

1069
01:07:33,770 --> 01:07:37,930
that you were the loveliest woman
I have ever known?

1070
01:07:38,010 --> 01:07:41,450
You know, there is a kind of envy
that is no way sinful.

1071
01:07:41,530 --> 01:07:44,050
That's what I've always
had for Matt all these years.

1072
01:07:44,130 --> 01:07:48,610
- What can I give you to drink?
- Well, I like Scotch if...

1073
01:07:48,690 --> 01:07:51,410
- Are we drinking wine?
- Yes.

1074
01:07:51,490 --> 01:07:54,450
Oh. I'll have
a little drop of Scotch anyhow.

1075
01:07:54,530 --> 01:07:57,250
Equal amount of soda, please.

1076
01:08:02,850 --> 01:08:04,610
Thank you.

1077
01:08:07,490 --> 01:08:09,810
My dear, what's the matter?

1078
01:08:12,410 --> 01:08:14,250
Sorry.

1079
01:08:14,330 --> 01:08:16,170
We're in trouble.

1080
01:08:17,210 --> 01:08:18,890
Mike...

1081
01:08:18,970 --> 01:08:22,090
we're in terrible trouble,
terrible trouble.

1082
01:08:22,170 --> 01:08:24,810
John told us...
Matt and me...

1083
01:08:24,890 --> 01:08:27,130
that he wouldn't marry Joey
unless we could say...

1084
01:08:27,170 --> 01:08:30,250
that we approved the marriage
with no reservations whatever.

1085
01:08:30,330 --> 01:08:32,610
Joey doesn't know
that he said that.

1086
01:08:32,690 --> 01:08:35,770
Now she's suddenly decided to go
with him tonight. She has her tickets.

1087
01:08:35,850 --> 01:08:39,330
The two of them are on their way in
from the airport with John's parents...

1088
01:08:39,410 --> 01:08:42,970
and neither of them knows
that Matt has decided...

1089
01:08:43,010 --> 01:08:44,010
Well.

1090
01:08:44,090 --> 01:08:46,890
Matt has decided
that he can't approve.

1091
01:08:46,970 --> 01:08:51,130
That's not true.
Please tell me it's not true.

1092
01:08:52,010 --> 01:08:54,330
- Where is Matt?
- He's upstairs changing. He's...

1093
01:08:56,170 --> 01:08:58,050
He's not himself.

1094
01:09:00,530 --> 01:09:02,490
Excuse me.

1095
01:09:02,570 --> 01:09:04,410
It's incredible!

1096
01:09:14,690 --> 01:09:16,930
- Table all right?
- It's fine.

1097
01:09:17,010 --> 01:09:20,290
- Thank you.
- Miss Christina, what's gonna happen?

1098
01:09:21,490 --> 01:09:24,210
I don't know, Tillie.

1099
01:09:24,290 --> 01:09:28,690
You and Mr. Matt, you gonna put a stop
to this damn nonsense foolishness?

1100
01:09:30,290 --> 01:09:32,770
I don't want to put a stop
to anything.

1101
01:09:32,850 --> 01:09:34,290
He's a fine man.

1102
01:09:34,370 --> 01:09:38,850
He's a wonderful man,
and Joey is very much in love with him.

1103
01:09:38,930 --> 01:09:42,090
And it isn't just
damn nonsense foolishness.

1104
01:09:42,170 --> 01:09:44,050
Well, I tell you, Miss Christina.

1105
01:09:44,130 --> 01:09:47,890
The way you are talkin',
I don't understand nothin' no more.

1106
01:09:50,810 --> 01:09:53,530
Nobody understands nothin' no more.

1107
01:09:55,130 --> 01:09:58,250
No, I don't think you're butting
into something that doesn't concern...

1108
01:09:59,610 --> 01:10:01,810
Damn blast these lousy laundries.

1109
01:10:01,890 --> 01:10:03,730
I understand how you feel.

1110
01:10:03,810 --> 01:10:06,490
I understand how everybody feels.

1111
01:10:06,530 --> 01:10:09,090
But you have to
understand something too.

1112
01:10:09,170 --> 01:10:11,370
They've boxed me
into a hell of a corner here.

1113
01:10:11,450 --> 01:10:13,810
And no matter what Christina says
or what you say...

1114
01:10:13,890 --> 01:10:16,170
I am not going to behave
irresponsibly.

1115
01:10:16,250 --> 01:10:19,770
I'm not gonna tell them they can't get
married. I don't have the right.

1116
01:10:19,850 --> 01:10:21,730
But they don't have the right
to come in here...

1117
01:10:21,770 --> 01:10:24,210
and expect me to be happy
about something any normal man...

1118
01:10:24,250 --> 01:10:26,090
Oh, for God's sake!

1119
01:10:27,130 --> 01:10:29,490
You're on the point of destroying
all the happiness there is...

1120
01:10:29,570 --> 01:10:32,770
in one of the happiest families
I've ever known.

1121
01:10:32,850 --> 01:10:34,890
Have you any appreciation
at all for Christina...

1122
01:10:36,770 --> 01:10:40,130
Have you any appreciation at all
of how that woman has behaved today?

1123
01:10:40,210 --> 01:10:44,290
From the moment they walked in, she was
for it, as if there were no problems.

1124
01:10:44,370 --> 01:10:48,370
But there are no problems that Joey
and young Prentice don't know about.

1125
01:10:48,450 --> 01:10:52,010
Christina has more respect for Joey's
judgment than you have. I must say...

1126
01:10:52,090 --> 01:10:54,570
Oh, come off it!

1127
01:10:54,650 --> 01:10:58,250
If Joey came home with some fuzzy-wuzzy
and said "This is the man for me"...

1128
01:10:58,330 --> 01:11:01,130
Christina would say,
"Oh, really? How wonderful.

1129
01:11:01,170 --> 01:11:04,770
Where will we get enough roses
to fill the Rose Bowl?"

1130
01:11:04,810 --> 01:11:08,090
I'm trying to remember
where I've seen you so angry.

1131
01:11:08,130 --> 01:11:11,570
Oh, yes. When you took
nine shots on the seventh green.

1132
01:11:13,130 --> 01:11:15,050
Would you mind
getting the hell out of here?

1133
01:11:15,090 --> 01:11:17,610
I think I know why you're angry too.

1134
01:11:17,690 --> 01:11:20,250
Not with the doctor,
whom you obviously respect.

1135
01:11:20,290 --> 01:11:23,290
Not with Joey or Christina,
not even with me.

1136
01:11:23,330 --> 01:11:25,330
You're angry with yourself.

1137
01:11:25,410 --> 01:11:27,330
You're a pontificating
old poop!

1138
01:11:27,410 --> 01:11:31,650
You're angry because all of a sudden,
and in a single day, you've been thrown.

1139
01:11:31,650 --> 01:11:35,210
You're the last man in the world I would
have expected to behave the way you are.

1140
01:11:35,290 --> 01:11:38,010
You're not yourself.
You're off balance.

1141
01:11:38,050 --> 01:11:40,290
You don't know who your are,
what you are or what you're doing.

1142
01:11:40,370 --> 01:11:41,850
That's your trouble.

1143
01:11:41,930 --> 01:11:45,490
You've gone back on yourself, laddie,
and in your heart you know it.

1144
01:11:45,570 --> 01:11:48,610
Now, listen, there's a limit
to what I'll take, even from you.

1145
01:11:48,690 --> 01:11:53,330
For 30 years, there's been no man
I've admired or respected more.

1146
01:11:53,410 --> 01:11:55,490
You know that.

1147
01:11:55,570 --> 01:12:00,410
And for the first time in all
those 30 years, I feel sorry for you.

1148
01:12:00,490 --> 01:12:02,930
Damn it, that's enough!

1149
01:12:03,010 --> 01:12:06,490
Are you really capable
of putting yourself in my position?

1150
01:12:06,570 --> 01:12:08,410
Unless you've got
some kids of your own...

1151
01:12:08,490 --> 01:12:10,730
hidden away somewhere
that haven't shown up in the record...

1152
01:12:10,810 --> 01:12:14,730
how can you possibly know how a father
would feel in a situation like this?

1153
01:12:14,770 --> 01:12:16,210
You don't know!

1154
01:12:16,290 --> 01:12:19,130
I happen to believe they wouldn't
have a dog's chance...

1155
01:12:19,210 --> 01:12:22,330
not in this country,
not in the whole, stinking world.

1156
01:12:22,370 --> 01:12:24,050
They are this country.

1157
01:12:24,090 --> 01:12:26,890
They'll change this stinking world.

1158
01:12:26,970 --> 01:12:29,770
Yeah, sure. Fifty years, maybe,
or a hundred years.

1159
01:12:29,850 --> 01:12:32,650
But not in your lifetime.
Maybe not even in mine.

1160
01:12:32,730 --> 01:12:34,050
My dear friend...

1161
01:12:34,130 --> 01:12:38,130
I wish with all my heart
you could be restrained.

1162
01:12:38,170 --> 01:12:40,010
And if I were ten years younger...

1163
01:12:40,090 --> 01:12:42,450
to prevent you
from going downstairs...

1164
01:12:42,530 --> 01:12:46,050
I believe I'd make some sort of effort
to wrestle you to the floor.

1165
01:12:46,130 --> 01:12:48,250
That'll be the day.

1166
01:12:51,450 --> 01:12:54,330
Is that the car?
Did you hear a car?

1167
01:12:59,170 --> 01:13:01,690
Mrs. Prentice,
I'm Christina Drayton.

1168
01:13:01,730 --> 01:13:04,090
- How do you do?
- How do you do, Mr. Prentice?

1169
01:13:04,170 --> 01:13:06,450
I'm so pleased to meet you.
Come on in.

1170
01:13:06,530 --> 01:13:09,250
Let me take your coat and hat.
And yours?

1171
01:13:09,330 --> 01:13:10,730
Thank you.

1172
01:13:10,810 --> 01:13:13,890
How good of you to come
all this long way to see us. Do go in.

1173
01:13:13,930 --> 01:13:16,570
What did Dad say? Did you tell him?
I'll bet he was shaken.

1174
01:13:16,610 --> 01:13:19,490
- It was a surprise.
- Does he want to talk to me?

1175
01:13:19,530 --> 01:13:23,130
Yes, I'm sure he does. Later.
Please come in.

1176
01:13:23,210 --> 01:13:26,050
May I get you a drink?
What would you like?

1177
01:13:26,090 --> 01:13:29,130
May I have some sherry, please?
What a lovely room.

1178
01:13:29,170 --> 01:13:31,650
Thank you. John, would you be bartender?
I'll have some sherry too.

1179
01:13:31,730 --> 01:13:34,130
- Of course.
- Shall we sit over here?

1180
01:13:34,210 --> 01:13:36,210
What will you have, Dad?
Bourbon?

1181
01:13:36,290 --> 01:13:40,530
- Thank you.
- You have such a magnificent view.

1182
01:13:40,570 --> 01:13:43,810
Thank you. Please sit down.
Sit down, Mr. Prentice.

1183
01:13:49,370 --> 01:13:51,530
Did you have a pleasant flight?

1184
01:13:51,570 --> 01:13:53,610
Very pleasant, thank you.

1185
01:13:53,690 --> 01:13:56,770
The view of the sunset
was breathtaking.

1186
01:13:56,810 --> 01:13:59,770
Only took forty minutes.
Four hundred miles.

1187
01:14:00,650 --> 01:14:02,450
It's incredible, isn't it?

1188
01:14:05,490 --> 01:14:08,490
My husband will be down directly,
I think.

1189
01:14:08,570 --> 01:14:10,170
He's upstairs changing.

1190
01:14:10,250 --> 01:14:12,730
And we have a friend of ours
who's coming to dinner with us.

1191
01:14:12,810 --> 01:14:14,490
Monsignor Ryan.

1192
01:14:14,570 --> 01:14:16,330
I'm sure theyll be down
in a minute.

1193
01:14:17,970 --> 01:14:19,290
- Thank you.
- Mom.

1194
01:14:19,370 --> 01:14:21,370
- Thank you.
- There you are, Dad.

1195
01:14:21,450 --> 01:14:23,810
Thanks, son.

1196
01:14:23,890 --> 01:14:27,010
Are you Catholics?

1197
01:14:28,250 --> 01:14:31,130
Well, no, we're not.

1198
01:14:31,210 --> 01:14:33,210
I'm afraid we're
nothing in particular.

1199
01:14:33,290 --> 01:14:36,530
Monsignor Ryan just happens to be
a very old friend.

1200
01:14:36,610 --> 01:14:40,210
Do you come often
to San Francisco?

1201
01:14:40,290 --> 01:14:42,530
I've got to talk to your father.

1202
01:14:42,610 --> 01:14:44,010
There he is.

1203
01:14:45,250 --> 01:14:48,690
Dad, I'd like you to meet
Mr. And Mrs. Prentice.

1204
01:14:48,770 --> 01:14:51,330
- This is my father.
- Mrs. Prentice, nice to meet you.

1205
01:14:51,410 --> 01:14:54,250
- How do you do?
- Mr. Prentice, happy to meet you.

1206
01:14:54,330 --> 01:14:57,010
- How do you do?
- May I present Monsignor Ryan?

1207
01:14:57,090 --> 01:14:59,370
- How do you do, ma'am?
- How do you do?

1208
01:14:59,450 --> 01:15:00,850
Glad to meet you, sir.

1209
01:15:00,930 --> 01:15:02,530
- Are you and John tending bar?
- Yes.

1210
01:15:02,610 --> 01:15:04,490
The monsignor and I
are both drinking Scotch.

1211
01:15:04,530 --> 01:15:06,410
Coming up.

1212
01:15:06,450 --> 01:15:08,330
Sit down.

1213
01:15:11,690 --> 01:15:12,650
Well.

1214
01:15:14,570 --> 01:15:16,810
Did you have a nice flight
from Los Angeles?

1215
01:15:16,890 --> 01:15:18,850
Oh, yes. Very nice flight.

1216
01:15:18,930 --> 01:15:20,650
Only 40 minutes.

1217
01:15:22,450 --> 01:15:24,330
Only 40 minutes from Los Angeles.

1218
01:15:24,370 --> 01:15:26,610
- Terrifying.
- If you're going to talk about flying...

1219
01:15:26,690 --> 01:15:28,650
you could talk
about flying to Geneva...

1220
01:15:28,730 --> 01:15:30,570
because John and I
are hoping to persuade...

1221
01:15:30,650 --> 01:15:32,650
all of you to fly over
for the wedding.

1222
01:15:32,730 --> 01:15:36,170
Would anybody like to talk about that
before I go up and start packing?

1223
01:15:37,930 --> 01:15:42,050
I take it they've told you
all about their plans?

1224
01:15:42,090 --> 01:15:45,450
Of course. It's only when you're
eloping that you keep it a secret.

1225
01:15:45,530 --> 01:15:47,490
I don't know about you,
Mr. Prentice...

1226
01:15:47,570 --> 01:15:51,210
but it seems to me that these two
are rushing it just a little bit.

1227
01:15:52,050 --> 01:15:54,450
It seemed that way to me too.

1228
01:15:55,290 --> 01:15:57,570
It seems like that to you too?

1229
01:15:57,650 --> 01:15:59,210
That's right.

1230
01:16:00,290 --> 01:16:02,490
I'm certainly relieved
to hear that.

1231
01:16:02,570 --> 01:16:05,610
I was beginning to think I was the only
one around here who had any...

1232
01:16:05,690 --> 01:16:08,690
I would like Mrs. Prentice
to see the view.

1233
01:16:08,770 --> 01:16:11,010
What the hell are you talking about?
What view?

1234
01:16:11,050 --> 01:16:13,330
From the terrace.
Before it gets too cold.

1235
01:16:13,410 --> 01:16:16,610
- Would you care to see the view?
- Oh, yes, thank you. I would.

1236
01:16:16,650 --> 01:16:19,130
Good. Excuse us.
Bring your drink with you.

1237
01:16:27,610 --> 01:16:31,890
Have you had any chance
to speak privately with John?

1238
01:16:31,930 --> 01:16:33,530
Well, no.

1239
01:16:33,610 --> 01:16:36,170
Because it's important that
you understand what's happened here...

1240
01:16:36,250 --> 01:16:39,770
and what I'm terribly afraid
is going to happen.

1241
01:16:39,810 --> 01:16:44,410
May I explain the situation to you
or try to?

1242
01:16:44,450 --> 01:16:46,050
Yes, please.
I wish you would.

1243
01:16:46,130 --> 01:16:48,370
First, I have to ask you...

1244
01:16:48,450 --> 01:16:51,570
Forgive my being so abrupt
and so direct.

1245
01:16:51,650 --> 01:16:55,170
Are you shocked
by the fact that John...

1246
01:16:55,250 --> 01:16:58,370
that your son is involved
with a white girl?

1247
01:16:58,450 --> 01:17:00,810
Surprised.

1248
01:17:00,850 --> 01:17:03,410
It never happened before.

1249
01:17:03,490 --> 01:17:06,490
I guess it never occurred to me
that such a thing might happen.

1250
01:17:07,930 --> 01:17:10,170
But it wouldn't be true
to say that I'm shocked.

1251
01:17:11,290 --> 01:17:13,130
Are you?

1252
01:17:14,330 --> 01:17:16,450
Well.

1253
01:17:16,490 --> 01:17:19,330
I think I was at first
this afternoon.

1254
01:17:20,330 --> 01:17:23,610
Because it came
as a complete surprise to us too.

1255
01:17:23,650 --> 01:17:25,570
But now I know
how they feel about each other.

1256
01:17:25,650 --> 01:17:28,130
Joey's still very young...

1257
01:17:28,210 --> 01:17:30,050
but she's not a child.

1258
01:17:31,490 --> 01:17:33,370
And they're...

1259
01:17:33,450 --> 01:17:35,370
deeply in love
with each other.

1260
01:17:39,530 --> 01:17:42,090
Are you about to tell me...

1261
01:17:42,170 --> 01:17:45,690
that you'd be willing to approve
the marriage but your husband won't?

1262
01:17:45,770 --> 01:17:47,610
Is that it?

1263
01:17:49,010 --> 01:17:50,850
Yes, that's it.

1264
01:17:50,930 --> 01:17:52,770
My husband won't either.

1265
01:17:55,170 --> 01:17:58,010
I wish there were more time...

1266
01:17:58,090 --> 01:18:01,370
if only so that we could adjust
to the situation.

1267
01:18:01,410 --> 01:18:04,730
But the way things are,
there just isn't any time.

1268
01:18:04,810 --> 01:18:08,730
If we're going to accept
the thing at all, it seems to me...

1269
01:18:08,810 --> 01:18:11,570
we'll have to trust
the two of them...

1270
01:18:11,650 --> 01:18:13,890
and accept that they know
what they're doing.

1271
01:18:14,930 --> 01:18:17,010
And, Mrs. Drayton...

1272
01:18:17,090 --> 01:18:19,490
my husband just won't do that.

1273
01:18:25,370 --> 01:18:27,850
They seem to be having
quite a conversation out there.

1274
01:18:29,290 --> 01:18:33,090
It might do no harm
if we could have a few words.

1275
01:18:33,130 --> 01:18:34,170
Yeah, sure.

1276
01:18:35,690 --> 01:18:38,330
We can go in my study.
Will you excuse us, please?

1277
01:18:50,250 --> 01:18:52,930
I'll have another drink
if you will, Doctor?

1278
01:18:57,650 --> 01:19:01,010
If you'll excuse me, I'll go up
and throw a few things together.

1279
01:19:01,090 --> 01:19:03,130
Like for the next ten years.

1280
01:19:12,050 --> 01:19:13,410
Mr. Drayton...

1281
01:19:15,170 --> 01:19:18,770
I don't know you at all, and
I certainly wouldn't want to offend you.

1282
01:19:18,850 --> 01:19:20,690
But are you some kind of a nut?

1283
01:19:20,770 --> 01:19:24,970
Are you going to tell me that you
approve of what's been going on here?

1284
01:19:25,010 --> 01:19:27,570
- I wasn't going to tell you that at all.
- Because if you do...

1285
01:19:27,650 --> 01:19:30,530
You may be a big, successful
newspaper publisher...

1286
01:19:30,570 --> 01:19:32,890
and I'm nothing but
a pensioned-off mailman...

1287
01:19:32,970 --> 01:19:34,970
but you are right out of your mind.

1288
01:19:42,730 --> 01:19:46,090
I have a pretty good idea
of what my father is saying to him.

1289
01:19:47,770 --> 01:19:50,330
But I wish I knew...

1290
01:19:50,410 --> 01:19:53,290
You were talking with him upstairs.

1291
01:19:53,370 --> 01:19:56,410
Have you any idea what
Mr. Drayton is saying to my father?

1292
01:19:57,690 --> 01:20:00,210
I can tell you one thing.
I was very sorry to hear...

1293
01:20:00,250 --> 01:20:03,410
that you intend
to withdraw from the situation...

1294
01:20:03,490 --> 01:20:06,450
if you encounter any opposition.

1295
01:20:20,650 --> 01:20:22,530
She's up there packing.

1296
01:20:25,730 --> 01:20:27,730
Your mother
would like to speak to you.

1297
01:20:33,890 --> 01:20:35,930
This is a mess.
Where's Joey?

1298
01:20:36,010 --> 01:20:37,850
- She's upstairs, my dear.
- I'm going up.

1299
01:20:38,890 --> 01:20:40,970
Everything is ready
whenever you all are ready.

1300
01:20:41,010 --> 01:20:42,890
We're not ready, Tillie.

1301
01:20:45,010 --> 01:20:46,410
Well!

1302
01:20:46,450 --> 01:20:50,050
What you're saying is that you feel
practically the same as I do about this.

1303
01:20:50,090 --> 01:20:52,650
That's right.
But even so...

1304
01:20:52,690 --> 01:20:57,330
this is a hell of an unhappy situation
for both your son and my daughter.

1305
01:20:59,330 --> 01:21:02,330
I think it would be best
if you talked to John yourself.

1306
01:21:12,130 --> 01:21:14,010
I said that...

1307
01:21:14,050 --> 01:21:17,010
if they didn't approve,
there'd be no marriage.

1308
01:21:20,090 --> 01:21:21,930
I set the terms, Mama.

1309
01:21:22,010 --> 01:21:23,610
They don't disapprove.

1310
01:21:24,850 --> 01:21:26,730
Only Mr. Drayton.

1311
01:21:26,810 --> 01:21:28,570
Are you sure?

1312
01:21:28,650 --> 01:21:31,970
She said she'd even drive
the two of you to the airport.

1313
01:21:36,970 --> 01:21:40,850
I've lived with your father
for almost 40 years.

1314
01:21:40,930 --> 01:21:42,570
God willing,
there'll be a lot more.

1315
01:21:44,770 --> 01:21:46,610
And even though...

1316
01:21:46,690 --> 01:21:49,970
I've only known about this situation
for one hour...

1317
01:21:51,010 --> 01:21:53,370
I feel the same way
Mrs. Drayton does.

1318
01:21:54,970 --> 01:21:57,930
She says Joanna
will never give you up.

1319
01:21:58,730 --> 01:22:00,130
I guess...

1320
01:22:00,210 --> 01:22:03,370
it depends upon
how much you want her.

1321
01:22:04,770 --> 01:22:06,650
Want her?

1322
01:22:08,850 --> 01:22:10,970
I want her, Mama.

1323
01:22:12,090 --> 01:22:15,170
You know what it's been like for me
these past eight years?

1324
01:22:16,570 --> 01:22:19,210
I felt like I never wanted
anybody again.

1325
01:22:19,250 --> 01:22:21,890
But, Mama...

1326
01:22:23,210 --> 01:22:26,290
these last few days with her...

1327
01:22:26,330 --> 01:22:29,850
it's like I'm alive again
and it's marvelous.

1328
01:22:30,890 --> 01:22:32,730
Excuse me, Doctor.

1329
01:22:36,410 --> 01:22:38,850
Your father wants to talk to you.

1330
01:22:38,930 --> 01:22:40,970
- Does he?
- He's in my study.

1331
01:23:00,410 --> 01:23:02,250
I've been talking to your husband.

1332
01:23:02,330 --> 01:23:05,490
He seems pretty much upset
by all this.

1333
01:23:05,570 --> 01:23:07,610
I know.

1334
01:23:07,650 --> 01:23:09,890
Your wife says you are too.

1335
01:23:09,970 --> 01:23:13,450
Not upset, exactly.
It's a very difficult problem.

1336
01:23:15,170 --> 01:23:17,930
For whom?
For you and my husband?

1337
01:23:19,490 --> 01:23:22,530
I think you'll solve your problem,
all right.

1338
01:23:22,610 --> 01:23:25,330
All you have to do is tell them
you're against them.

1339
01:23:25,410 --> 01:23:26,490
That's all.

1340
01:23:26,570 --> 01:23:28,410
And you'll have no problem.

1341
01:23:30,890 --> 01:23:34,010
You're not going to tell me
you're happy about this relationship?

1342
01:23:35,250 --> 01:23:38,890
This is not a night
for talking about happiness.

1343
01:23:38,930 --> 01:23:40,850
This is an unhappy night.

1344
01:23:42,210 --> 01:23:45,730
You've been talking to Christina.
I know how she feels.

1345
01:23:45,810 --> 01:23:49,930
Can you imagine for one minute that
I want to see either one of them hurt?

1346
01:23:52,930 --> 01:23:55,890
No more than my husband does.

1347
01:23:55,970 --> 01:23:58,610
But hurt they're going to be.

1348
01:24:00,330 --> 01:24:02,210
Worse than my husband knows.

1349
01:24:03,530 --> 01:24:05,810
I think worse than you know too.

1350
01:24:08,650 --> 01:24:10,930
I tell you he's as much
against this thing as I am.

1351
01:24:10,970 --> 01:24:12,410
Maybe more!

1352
01:24:12,490 --> 01:24:14,770
Son, you've got to listen to me.

1353
01:24:14,850 --> 01:24:17,570
I'm not trying to tell you
how to live your life...

1354
01:24:17,650 --> 01:24:20,450
but you've never
made a mistake like this before.

1355
01:24:20,530 --> 01:24:22,450
You've been nothin'
but a source of pride...

1356
01:24:22,530 --> 01:24:24,610
for me and your mother
your whole life.

1357
01:24:24,650 --> 01:24:26,650
But you don't know what you're doin'.

1358
01:24:26,730 --> 01:24:29,090
This affair here...
It all happened too fast.

1359
01:24:29,170 --> 01:24:31,010
You said so yourself.

1360
01:24:31,090 --> 01:24:33,450
But you've got to stop and think.

1361
01:24:33,530 --> 01:24:35,850
Have you thought what people
would say about you?

1362
01:24:35,930 --> 01:24:39,610
In 16 or 17 states you'd
be breakin' the law. You'd be criminals.

1363
01:24:39,690 --> 01:24:41,570
And say they changed the law.

1364
01:24:41,650 --> 01:24:44,450
That don't change
the way people feel about this thing.

1365
01:24:44,530 --> 01:24:47,330
For a man who all his life never
put a wrong foot anywhere...

1366
01:24:47,410 --> 01:24:48,850
you're way out of line!

1367
01:24:48,930 --> 01:24:51,330
That's for me to decide, man.

1368
01:24:51,410 --> 01:24:54,330
- So just shut up and let me...
- You don't say that to me!

1369
01:24:54,410 --> 01:24:56,890
You haven't got the right to ever say
a thing like that to me.

1370
01:24:56,970 --> 01:24:58,970
Not after what I've been to you!

1371
01:24:59,050 --> 01:25:01,130
And you know that,
and I know that.

1372
01:25:01,210 --> 01:25:03,530
Yeah, I know what you are
and what you've made of yourself.

1373
01:25:03,610 --> 01:25:07,250
But I worked my ass off to get the money
to buy you all the chances you had!

1374
01:25:07,330 --> 01:25:11,450
You know how far
I carried that bag in 30 years?

1375
01:25:11,530 --> 01:25:13,810
75,000 miles.

1376
01:25:13,890 --> 01:25:17,130
And mowin' lawns in the dark so you
wouldn't have to be stokin' furnaces...

1377
01:25:17,210 --> 01:25:19,530
and could bear down on the books.

1378
01:25:20,490 --> 01:25:24,330
There were things your mother should
have had that she insisted go for you.

1379
01:25:24,410 --> 01:25:26,410
And I don't mean fancy things.

1380
01:25:26,490 --> 01:25:29,210
I mean a decent coat.
A lousy coat!

1381
01:25:29,290 --> 01:25:31,330
And you're gonna tell me
that means nothin' to you...

1382
01:25:31,410 --> 01:25:33,250
and you could
break your mother's heart?

1383
01:25:37,170 --> 01:25:40,450
What happens to men
when they grow old?

1384
01:25:41,930 --> 01:25:43,770
Why do they forget everything?

1385
01:25:44,930 --> 01:25:46,810
I believe...

1386
01:25:46,850 --> 01:25:50,450
those two young people
need each other...

1387
01:25:50,490 --> 01:25:53,610
like they need
the air to breathe in.

1388
01:25:53,690 --> 01:25:57,090
Anybody can see that
by just looking at them.

1389
01:25:58,250 --> 01:26:00,730
But you and my husband are...

1390
01:26:00,770 --> 01:26:03,850
You might as well be blind men.

1391
01:26:03,930 --> 01:26:06,850
You can only see
that they have a problem.

1392
01:26:08,570 --> 01:26:11,770
But do you really know
what's happened to them?

1393
01:26:11,850 --> 01:26:13,690
How they feel about each other?

1394
01:26:16,210 --> 01:26:17,650
I believe...

1395
01:26:17,690 --> 01:26:20,490
that men grow old.

1396
01:26:20,570 --> 01:26:22,330
And when the...

1397
01:26:22,370 --> 01:26:26,090
When sexual things no longer matter
to them, they forget it all.

1398
01:26:27,370 --> 01:26:30,330
Forget what true passion is.

1399
01:26:33,090 --> 01:26:35,690
If you ever felt what my son...

1400
01:26:38,130 --> 01:26:40,930
feels for your daughter,
you've forgotten everything about it.

1401
01:26:41,010 --> 01:26:43,170
My husband too.

1402
01:26:43,250 --> 01:26:45,130
You knew once...

1403
01:26:45,210 --> 01:26:47,050
but that was a long time ago.

1404
01:26:47,130 --> 01:26:49,010
Now the two of you don't know.

1405
01:26:49,770 --> 01:26:53,250
And the strange thing...

1406
01:26:53,330 --> 01:26:55,290
for your wife and me...

1407
01:26:55,370 --> 01:26:59,570
is that you don't even remember.

1408
01:27:00,650 --> 01:27:02,490
If you did...

1409
01:27:02,530 --> 01:27:04,810
how could you do
what you are doing?

1410
01:27:11,290 --> 01:27:14,410
I don't care what your mother says.
Maybe she's gone haywire too.

1411
01:27:14,490 --> 01:27:16,050
This is between you and me.

1412
01:27:16,130 --> 01:27:18,490
That's the first thing you've said
that makes any sense...

1413
01:27:18,530 --> 01:27:20,010
because that's exactly where it's at.

1414
01:27:20,090 --> 01:27:22,610
- And what I mean to say is...
- You've said what you had to say.

1415
01:27:24,170 --> 01:27:26,010
You listen to me.

1416
01:27:29,410 --> 01:27:32,650
You say you don't want to tell me
how to live my life?

1417
01:27:32,730 --> 01:27:34,250
What do you think
you've been doing?

1418
01:27:34,330 --> 01:27:36,610
You tell me what rights I've got
or haven't got...

1419
01:27:36,650 --> 01:27:38,770
and what I owe to you
for what you've done for me.

1420
01:27:40,970 --> 01:27:42,970
Let me tell you something.

1421
01:27:43,050 --> 01:27:45,650
I owe you nothing.

1422
01:27:45,690 --> 01:27:47,970
If you carried that bag
a million miles...

1423
01:27:48,050 --> 01:27:50,730
you did what you
were supposed to do...

1424
01:27:50,810 --> 01:27:53,370
because you brought me
into this world...

1425
01:27:53,450 --> 01:27:55,890
and from that day you owed me...

1426
01:27:55,970 --> 01:27:58,410
everything you could ever do for me,
like I will owe my son...

1427
01:27:58,490 --> 01:27:59,770
if I ever have another.

1428
01:27:59,850 --> 01:28:02,410
But you don't own me.

1429
01:28:02,490 --> 01:28:05,690
You can't tell me when or where
I'm out of line...

1430
01:28:05,770 --> 01:28:08,970
or try to get me to live my life
according to your rules.

1431
01:28:09,050 --> 01:28:10,890
You don't even know
what I am, Dad.

1432
01:28:10,970 --> 01:28:15,010
You don't know who I am,
how I feel, what I think.

1433
01:28:15,050 --> 01:28:18,770
And if I tried to explain it the rest of
your life, you would never understand.

1434
01:28:19,810 --> 01:28:22,690
You are 30 years older than I am.

1435
01:28:22,770 --> 01:28:24,890
You and your whole lousy generation...

1436
01:28:24,970 --> 01:28:27,850
believes the way it was for you
is the way it's got to be!

1437
01:28:27,930 --> 01:28:30,850
And not until your whole generation
has lain down and died...

1438
01:28:30,930 --> 01:28:33,930
will the deadweight of you
be off our backs!

1439
01:28:34,010 --> 01:28:36,970
You understand?
You've got to get off my back.

1440
01:28:54,450 --> 01:28:56,330
Dad.

1441
01:29:02,850 --> 01:29:04,690
You're my father.

1442
01:29:05,730 --> 01:29:07,970
I'm your son.
I love you.

1443
01:29:09,010 --> 01:29:11,730
I always have
and I always will.

1444
01:29:13,890 --> 01:29:16,770
But you think of yourself
as a colored man.

1445
01:29:18,330 --> 01:29:20,250
I think of myself...

1446
01:29:20,290 --> 01:29:22,170
as a man.

1447
01:29:27,930 --> 01:29:30,850
Now, I've got a decision to make.

1448
01:29:31,850 --> 01:29:34,050
And I've got to make it alone.

1449
01:29:34,130 --> 01:29:35,970
And I gotta make it in a hurry.

1450
01:29:36,810 --> 01:29:38,650
So...

1451
01:29:40,010 --> 01:29:42,170
would you go out there...

1452
01:29:42,250 --> 01:29:44,090
and see after my mother?

1453
01:30:36,650 --> 01:30:39,610
You've just got to talk John's parents
into flying over with you.

1454
01:30:39,690 --> 01:30:41,570
It would mean so much to John
to have them there...

1455
01:30:41,650 --> 01:30:44,090
and I know they can afford it.

1456
01:30:44,170 --> 01:30:47,290
You know, I think John's father
is gonna make it a bit rough for him.

1457
01:30:47,330 --> 01:30:50,970
Did you see his expression when he
walked off to have a talk with Dad?

1458
01:30:51,010 --> 01:30:52,810
But isn't she lovely?

1459
01:30:52,890 --> 01:30:55,210
- Don't you like her already?
- Yes, darling, I do.

1460
01:30:55,250 --> 01:30:56,850
She's a good one.

1461
01:30:56,930 --> 01:30:59,210
When John's father first saw
that I was a white girl...

1462
01:30:59,290 --> 01:31:01,130
I thought he was going to faint.

1463
01:31:01,210 --> 01:31:03,330
What about your father?

1464
01:31:03,410 --> 01:31:06,410
Yes, that was funny, wasn't it?

1465
01:31:06,490 --> 01:31:09,770
Oh, Mom, isn't this thrilling?
Aren't you just...

1466
01:31:09,850 --> 01:31:11,970
Yes, darling, I am. Just.

1467
01:31:58,890 --> 01:32:01,650
I should be able to say something
to you, Mrs. Prentice.

1468
01:32:02,850 --> 01:32:07,130
In my trade, there are
a hundred clich phrases of comfort...

1469
01:32:07,210 --> 01:32:09,890
for every human condition.

1470
01:32:09,970 --> 01:32:13,450
But in the midst
of this heartbreaking distress...

1471
01:32:13,530 --> 01:32:15,410
I must admit...

1472
01:32:15,450 --> 01:32:17,330
I'm completely stumped.

1473
01:32:18,490 --> 01:32:20,330
There's simply
nothing I could say.

1474
01:32:24,050 --> 01:32:26,010
Mary, you've just got to understand...

1475
01:32:26,090 --> 01:32:29,050
Please, John.
The monsignor is right.

1476
01:32:29,130 --> 01:32:30,970
Please say no more.

1477
01:32:52,330 --> 01:32:54,170
I'll be a son of a bitch.

1478
01:33:13,690 --> 01:33:15,530
Close the door, Mr. Drayton.

1479
01:33:25,570 --> 01:33:28,210
You didn't have the guts
to tell me face-to-face, did you?

1480
01:33:29,250 --> 01:33:31,970
Before you start telling me
how much guts I've got...

1481
01:33:32,050 --> 01:33:35,290
I told you
I'd have something to say.

1482
01:33:35,370 --> 01:33:37,210
Now I'm ready to say it.

1483
01:33:38,970 --> 01:33:40,930
Are you gonna stay in here?

1484
01:33:55,610 --> 01:33:59,530
You know that I'm
completely sympathetic, don't you?

1485
01:33:59,610 --> 01:34:03,090
You know that I have
no reservations about anything.

1486
01:34:03,130 --> 01:34:06,330
And that whatever makes you happy
is my happiness too.

1487
01:34:06,410 --> 01:34:08,250
Of course I know that.

1488
01:34:09,410 --> 01:34:12,490
Then listen to me, darling.

1489
01:34:12,570 --> 01:34:15,050
There's something
I have to tell you...

1490
01:34:15,130 --> 01:34:17,210
about this situation...

1491
01:34:17,250 --> 01:34:20,130
which you don't really...

1492
01:34:20,170 --> 01:34:21,330
What are you doing up there?

1493
01:34:21,410 --> 01:34:24,410
Come on down here, both of you!

1494
01:34:26,250 --> 01:34:28,090
How about your glasses?

1495
01:34:28,170 --> 01:34:31,090
- Can I get you a drink?
- No, thank you.

1496
01:34:33,170 --> 01:34:35,010
No, you've had
enough as it is already.

1497
01:34:35,090 --> 01:34:36,850
What's going on?

1498
01:34:36,930 --> 01:34:39,170
There's something I want to say
and I'd like you to sit down...

1499
01:34:39,250 --> 01:34:41,450
see if you can keep quiet
for once in your life.

1500
01:34:41,490 --> 01:34:43,490
Please, sit down, John.

1501
01:34:43,570 --> 01:34:45,410
Sit down, Chris, please.

1502
01:34:47,330 --> 01:34:50,610
I have a few things to say and
you might just think they're important.

1503
01:34:52,730 --> 01:34:56,130
This has been a strange day. I don't
think that's putting it too strongly.

1504
01:34:56,210 --> 01:34:58,850
I might even say
it's been an extraordinary day.

1505
01:35:00,130 --> 01:35:02,610
I've been out there
thinking about the day...

1506
01:35:02,690 --> 01:35:04,610
and the way it has gone...

1507
01:35:04,690 --> 01:35:07,570
and it seems to me that now...

1508
01:35:07,650 --> 01:35:11,210
I need to make a few
personal statements.

1509
01:35:11,290 --> 01:35:13,610
For a variety of reasons.

1510
01:35:17,570 --> 01:35:21,690
The day began for me when I walked into
this house and Tillie said to me...

1511
01:35:23,210 --> 01:35:24,210
Excuse me.

1512
01:35:25,450 --> 01:35:27,890
Tillie!
This'll only take a second.

1513
01:35:27,970 --> 01:35:30,530
- Everything's been ready for...
- I know.

1514
01:35:30,570 --> 01:35:32,450
All right. Sit down.

1515
01:35:33,650 --> 01:35:35,330
This is Miss Matilda Binks...

1516
01:35:35,410 --> 01:35:38,690
who's been a member of this family
for 22 years...

1517
01:35:38,770 --> 01:35:41,770
and who today has been
making a great deal of trouble.

1518
01:35:41,850 --> 01:35:42,930
Sit down, Tillie.

1519
01:35:45,930 --> 01:35:50,490
Now. The minute I walked
into this house this afternoon...

1520
01:35:50,570 --> 01:35:55,570
Miss Binks said to me,
"Well, all hell's done broke loose now."

1521
01:35:55,650 --> 01:35:58,090
I asked her, naturally enough,
to what she referred...

1522
01:35:58,170 --> 01:36:00,370
and she said, "You'll see."

1523
01:36:00,450 --> 01:36:02,010
And I did.

1524
01:36:03,010 --> 01:36:07,650
Then after some preliminary guessing
games, at which I was never very good...

1525
01:36:07,690 --> 01:36:10,570
it was explained to me
by my daughter...

1526
01:36:10,650 --> 01:36:12,970
that she intended to get married.

1527
01:36:13,050 --> 01:36:17,410
And that her intended was a young man
whom I had never met...

1528
01:36:17,490 --> 01:36:20,370
who happened to be a Negro.

1529
01:36:20,410 --> 01:36:24,730
I think it's fair to say
that I responded to this news...

1530
01:36:24,810 --> 01:36:27,850
in the same manner that any
normal father would respond to it...

1531
01:36:27,890 --> 01:36:30,770
unless, of course, his daughter
happened to be a Negro too.

1532
01:36:32,810 --> 01:36:37,130
In a word, I was flabbergasted. And
while I was still being flabbergasted...

1533
01:36:37,210 --> 01:36:39,890
I was informed by my daughter...

1534
01:36:39,970 --> 01:36:41,930
a very determined young woman...

1535
01:36:41,970 --> 01:36:43,970
much like her mother...

1536
01:36:44,050 --> 01:36:47,290
that the marriage was on...

1537
01:36:47,370 --> 01:36:50,130
no matter what her mother and I
might feel about it.

1538
01:36:52,130 --> 01:36:56,970
Then the next startling development
occurred when you walked in...

1539
01:36:57,050 --> 01:36:59,450
and said that unless we...
her mother and I...

1540
01:36:59,530 --> 01:37:02,850
approved of the marriage,
there would be no marriage.

1541
01:37:02,930 --> 01:37:04,970
You didn't!
What a funny thing to do.

1542
01:37:08,210 --> 01:37:11,050
This may be the last chance
I'll ever have...

1543
01:37:11,130 --> 01:37:13,210
to tell you to do anything.

1544
01:37:13,210 --> 01:37:15,530
So I'm telling you
shut up.

1545
01:37:19,210 --> 01:37:21,130
Now.

1546
01:37:21,210 --> 01:37:25,170
It became clear that we had one
single day to make up our minds...

1547
01:37:25,250 --> 01:37:28,450
as to how we felt
about this whole situation.

1548
01:37:28,490 --> 01:37:29,730
So what happened?

1549
01:37:29,810 --> 01:37:31,970
My wife, typically enough...

1550
01:37:32,010 --> 01:37:33,850
decided to simply ignore...

1551
01:37:33,930 --> 01:37:36,650
every practical aspect
of the situation...

1552
01:37:36,730 --> 01:37:40,170
and was carried away
in some kind of romantic haze...

1553
01:37:40,250 --> 01:37:41,850
which made her, in my view...

1554
01:37:41,930 --> 01:37:45,490
totally inaccessible
to anything in the way of reason.

1555
01:37:48,370 --> 01:37:52,410
Now I have not as yet referred
to His Reverence...

1556
01:37:52,450 --> 01:37:55,850
who began by forcing his way
into the situation...

1557
01:37:55,890 --> 01:37:58,170
and then insulting my intelligence...,.

1558
01:37:58,210 --> 01:38:00,930
By mouthing 300 platitudes...

1559
01:38:01,010 --> 01:38:04,410
and ending just a half hour ago
by coming to my room...

1560
01:38:04,490 --> 01:38:07,850
and challenging me
to a wrestling match.

1561
01:38:07,930 --> 01:38:11,370
- What time is your plane?
- 10:45.

1562
01:38:12,410 --> 01:38:13,850
Right.

1563
01:38:13,930 --> 01:38:15,970
Now, Mr. Prentice...

1564
01:38:16,010 --> 01:38:18,410
clearly a most reasonable man...

1565
01:38:18,490 --> 01:38:20,330
says he has no wish to offend me...

1566
01:38:20,410 --> 01:38:22,530
but wants to know
if I'm some kind of a nut.

1567
01:38:24,410 --> 01:38:26,250
And Mrs. Prentice says...

1568
01:38:26,290 --> 01:38:29,210
that like her husband,
I'm a burnt-out old shell of a man...

1569
01:38:29,250 --> 01:38:32,370
who cannot even
remember what it's like...

1570
01:38:32,450 --> 01:38:34,090
to love a woman...

1571
01:38:35,210 --> 01:38:37,930
the way her son loves my daughter.

1572
01:38:42,610 --> 01:38:44,650
And strange as it seems...

1573
01:38:46,410 --> 01:38:49,290
that's the first statement
made to me all day...

1574
01:38:49,330 --> 01:38:51,690
with which I am prepared
to take issue.

1575
01:38:54,930 --> 01:38:57,170
Because I think you're wrong.

1576
01:38:57,210 --> 01:38:59,570
You're as wrong as you can be.

1577
01:39:00,690 --> 01:39:04,370
I admit that I hadn't considered it,
hadn't even thought about it...

1578
01:39:04,410 --> 01:39:07,930
but I know exactly
how he feels about her.

1579
01:39:08,970 --> 01:39:11,570
And there is nothing,
absolutely nothing...

1580
01:39:11,650 --> 01:39:14,930
that your son feels
for my daughter...

1581
01:39:14,970 --> 01:39:17,210
that I didn't feel for Christina.

1582
01:39:19,730 --> 01:39:21,690
Old? Yes.

1583
01:39:21,770 --> 01:39:23,650
Burnt out? Certainly.

1584
01:39:24,730 --> 01:39:27,930
But I can tell you
the memories are still there...

1585
01:39:29,250 --> 01:39:32,770
clear, intact, indestructible.

1586
01:39:33,890 --> 01:39:36,810
And they'll be there
if I live to be 110.

1587
01:39:36,890 --> 01:39:39,450
Where John
made his mistake, I think...

1588
01:39:39,530 --> 01:39:43,090
was attaching so much importance
to what her mother and I might think.

1589
01:39:43,130 --> 01:39:48,050
Because in the final analysis,
it doesn't matter a damn what we think.

1590
01:39:48,130 --> 01:39:51,290
The only thing that matters
is what they feel...

1591
01:39:51,370 --> 01:39:53,930
and how much they feel...

1592
01:39:54,010 --> 01:39:55,850
for each other.

1593
01:39:59,330 --> 01:40:01,570
And if it's half...

1594
01:40:01,650 --> 01:40:03,490
of what we felt...

1595
01:40:07,050 --> 01:40:08,970
that's everything.

1596
01:40:22,530 --> 01:40:24,810
As for you two and
the problems you're going to have...

1597
01:40:24,850 --> 01:40:28,250
they seem almost unimaginable.

1598
01:40:28,330 --> 01:40:30,450
But you'll have no problem with me.

1599
01:40:31,770 --> 01:40:33,290
And I think...

1600
01:40:33,370 --> 01:40:36,050
that when Christina and I
and your mother...

1601
01:40:36,130 --> 01:40:38,050
have some time to work on him...

1602
01:40:38,130 --> 01:40:40,330
you'll have no problem
with your father.

1603
01:40:43,970 --> 01:40:47,210
But you do know...
I'm sure you know...

1604
01:40:47,250 --> 01:40:49,570
what you're up against.

1605
01:40:49,570 --> 01:40:52,930
There'll be a hundred million people
right here in this country...

1606
01:40:53,010 --> 01:40:55,090
who'll be shocked and offended...

1607
01:40:55,170 --> 01:40:57,690
and appalled at the two of you.

1608
01:40:59,850 --> 01:41:02,890
And the two of you will just
have to ride that out.

1609
01:41:02,970 --> 01:41:05,490
Maybe every day
for the rest of your lives.

1610
01:41:07,490 --> 01:41:10,570
You can try to ignore those people...

1611
01:41:10,650 --> 01:41:13,650
or you can feel sorry for them
and for their prejudices...

1612
01:41:13,730 --> 01:41:18,690
and their bigotry and
their blind hatreds and stupid fears.

1613
01:41:18,770 --> 01:41:20,610
But where necessary...

1614
01:41:20,690 --> 01:41:24,210
you'll just have
to cling tight to each other...

1615
01:41:24,290 --> 01:41:27,170
and say screw all those people!

1616
01:41:28,210 --> 01:41:32,650
Anybody could make a hell of a
good case against your getting married.

1617
01:41:33,530 --> 01:41:36,570
The arguments are so obvious
that nobody has to make them.

1618
01:41:38,010 --> 01:41:39,850
But you're two wonderful people...

1619
01:41:41,690 --> 01:41:43,570
who happened to fall in love...

1620
01:41:44,890 --> 01:41:48,010
and happen to have
a pigmentation problem.

1621
01:41:48,930 --> 01:41:51,210
And I think that now...

1622
01:41:51,290 --> 01:41:53,450
no matter what kind of a case
some bastard could make...

1623
01:41:53,530 --> 01:41:55,370
against your getting married...

1624
01:41:55,450 --> 01:41:57,290
there would be only one thing worse.

1625
01:41:58,770 --> 01:42:01,170
And that would be if...

1626
01:42:01,250 --> 01:42:03,410
knowing what you two are...

1627
01:42:03,490 --> 01:42:05,570
knowing what you two have...

1628
01:42:05,650 --> 01:42:08,730
and knowing what you two feel...

1629
01:42:08,810 --> 01:42:10,930
you didn't get married.

1630
01:42:30,930 --> 01:42:33,530
Well, Tillie, when the hell
are we gonna get some dinner?